{
  "texts": [
    "In Fig. 6, we compare 2017 and 2018 coherently averaged visibilities on the same triangles (or similar ones) selected in 2017, where day-to-day variability of closure phases was observed (see Fig.",
    "14 in M 87 * 2017 III).",
    "Here we also include a wide GLT triangle whose closure phases deviate from zero, indicating the presence of resolved asymmetric structure, similar to what has been observed in other triangles in 2017 before the inclusion of the GLT in the EHT array (M 87 * 2017 III).",
    "Gray circles and red diamonds in Fig. 6 show closure phase measurements from two days in 2017, and blue squares show closure phases measured in 2018.",
    "While some triangles show some small deviations in closure phase between days in 2017, the 2018 closure phases are qualitatively different, demonstrating clear indications of different asymmetric structure in the 2018 data."
  ]
}